01:17.318 --> 01:19.422
_

01:20.551 --> 01:22.550
...is they permeate your essence.

01:22.551 --> 01:23.550
I am so sorry.

01:23.551 --> 01:25.550
The maestro's not usually like that.

01:25.551 --> 01:27.550
He's just, um...

01:27.551 --> 01:29.550
He's under a bit of stress lately.

01:29.551 --> 01:32.550
No, no, no. It's all happiness, brah.

01:32.551 --> 01:34.550
He was fantastic.

01:34.551 --> 01:36.550
There we are. Now give a look to the clock.

01:36.551 --> 01:38.550
Turn back time with your eyes.

01:38.551 --> 01:41.550
Yes. There we are. You're not
going to be deterred, are you?

01:41.551 --> 01:42.550
So let me ask you,

01:42.551 --> 01:44.550
how does your personal
life inform your work?

01:44.551 --> 01:46.550
- Uh...
- Maestro.

01:46.551 --> 01:47.550
Hmm? Oh, thank you.

01:47.551 --> 01:48.550
Sure.

01:48.551 --> 01:51.550
- I've never thought about that.
- Yeah.

01:51.551 --> 01:53.550
I don't think about those things.

01:53.551 --> 01:55.550
I actually find them quite idiotic.

01:55.551 --> 01:57.550
Maestros.

01:57.551 --> 01:59.550
Can't live with them,

01:59.551 --> 02:03.550
can't run a major orchestra without them.

02:03.551 --> 02:05.550
Thank you for being part
of the photo shoot.

02:05.551 --> 02:09.550
Listen Cynthia, you're an
asset to this orchestra

02:09.550 --> 02:11.550
in so many ways, even more so now

02:11.551 --> 02:14.550
that you're chairwoman of
the Players' Committee.

02:14.551 --> 02:16.760
Orchestra admires you so,

02:16.761 --> 02:19.550
as do I.

02:19.551 --> 02:20.550
That's great to hear

02:20.551 --> 02:22.550
because I would love your support

02:22.551 --> 02:23.911
in the upcoming negotiations.

02:26.551 --> 02:28.550
We have a lot in common, you and I.

02:28.551 --> 02:34.469
We're both fans of genius,
conductors specifically.

02:34.470 --> 02:37.550
You were a fan of Karzoff in Moscow

02:37.551 --> 02:40.550
and then of dear Thomas from '95 to '98

02:40.551 --> 02:41.913
when he was at the London Phil,

02:41.914 --> 02:43.550
and then Carlotta Di Gozzi...

02:43.551 --> 02:45.550
It's so hard to find great
female conductors...

02:45.551 --> 02:50.550
and then of Thomas again.

02:50.551 --> 02:52.550
And they were fans of mine,

02:52.551 --> 02:54.550
not that it's any of your business.

02:54.551 --> 02:57.550
[Rodrigo shouting in Spanish]

02:57.551 --> 02:58.550
He's quite a handful.

02:58.551 --> 03:02.550
Do you see this trench in my forehead?

03:02.551 --> 03:03.551
This... This is new.

03:03.552 --> 03:06.550
These strong genius big shots,

03:06.551 --> 03:09.550
they're just... they're just really

03:09.551 --> 03:11.550
overgrown babies, aren't they?

03:11.551 --> 03:13.550
Throwing tantrums. "I want this.

03:13.551 --> 03:15.550
Give me that. You don't understand me."

03:15.551 --> 03:17.550
Even if you do understand them,

03:17.551 --> 03:20.550
they don't believe that you do.

03:20.551 --> 03:22.550
But not with you, Cynthia.

03:22.551 --> 03:24.550
They know you understand them,

03:24.551 --> 03:26.751
therefore they trust you.

03:27.551 --> 03:31.550
This dynamic could be very helpful to us.

03:31.551 --> 03:33.550
What do you want?

03:33.551 --> 03:35.550
Stay close to him.

03:35.551 --> 03:38.550
In return, my door will always be open.

03:38.551 --> 03:40.427
These are challenging times.

03:40.428 --> 03:43.550
We both want this institution to survive.

03:43.551 --> 03:45.550
The difference is you look at the orchestra

03:45.551 --> 03:46.819
and you see an institution.

03:46.820 --> 03:49.550
I see musicians, and I
think the audience...

03:49.551 --> 03:51.550
Audience sees one thing: our new maest...

03:51.551 --> 03:54.550
I am not going to talk about her, okay?

03:54.551 --> 03:56.550
No! Okay?

03:56.551 --> 03:58.550
Is there a problem over here, maestro?

03:58.551 --> 04:00.550
No. We found the solution.

04:00.551 --> 04:01.550
Oh, great.

04:01.551 --> 04:02.550
The interview's over.

04:02.551 --> 04:04.052
Ciao.

04:04.053 --> 04:07.177
Hailey, put that sign up now.

04:07.178 --> 04:08.751
Hah. Huh?

04:19.551 --> 04:21.550
I didn't sleep with Rodrigo.

04:21.551 --> 04:22.550
Anything else?

04:22.551 --> 04:24.550
I really want to take lessons from you.

04:24.551 --> 04:26.550
What are you, some kind of masochist?

04:26.551 --> 04:27.550
Maybe. I don't know.

04:27.551 --> 04:29.550
Don't you kind of have
to be to play the oboe?

04:29.551 --> 04:32.550
Look, you're the best there
is in New York City,

04:32.551 --> 04:35.550
and you're the only shot I have
at coming any closer to this.

04:35.551 --> 04:37.550
You're right, I am the best,

04:37.551 --> 04:39.550
and some of that rubs off on my students,

04:39.551 --> 04:41.550
but I'm no miracle worker.

04:41.551 --> 04:43.550
I'm good. I'm better than I showed,

04:43.551 --> 04:45.550
and I'm willing to make sacrifices.

04:45.551 --> 04:48.550
What do you want, a medal? I'm expensive.

04:48.551 --> 04:50.550
I don't care.

04:50.551 --> 04:51.550
$400 an hour.

04:51.551 --> 04:52.550
Holy shit. What?

04:52.551 --> 04:54.550
No. Uh, I can make that work.

04:54.551 --> 04:55.550
When do we start?

04:55.551 --> 04:57.550
I didn't say yes.

04:57.551 --> 04:59.751
If I feel like it, I'll let you know.

05:00.551 --> 05:01.551
What the hell is going on?

05:01.552 --> 05:03.550
My commute takes 45 minutes.

05:03.551 --> 05:05.550
- What?- This is bullshit.

05:05.551 --> 05:08.550
"Rehearsal today is cancelled"?

05:08.551 --> 05:10.751
"Bring a sweater"?

05:12.551 --> 05:15.550
Okay, you're going to want to
pull the corners of your mouth in

05:15.551 --> 05:17.550
so that you're fully supporting the reed.

05:17.551 --> 05:19.550
- Good. That's really good.
- [cell phone jangles]

05:19.551 --> 05:20.751
Uh...

05:24.551 --> 05:26.550
And then you're going to want to inhale

05:26.551 --> 05:28.550
and then create a steady stream of air.

05:28.551 --> 05:31.550
Hailey, Tim's finally
going to get circumcised.

05:31.551 --> 05:33.550
He's going in tomorrow.
Should we bring him soup?

05:33.551 --> 05:37.550
Lizzie, meet Duncan. He's 12. Put pants on.

05:37.551 --> 05:38.550
Oh, for fuck's sake.

05:38.551 --> 05:40.751
- Sorry about that.
- [Cell phone jangles]

05:41.551 --> 05:42.751
Not a problem.

05:44.551 --> 05:45.550
You going to get that?

05:45.551 --> 05:46.550
- No.
- [jangling]

05:46.551 --> 05:48.550
- Is it Alex?
- Yeah.

05:48.551 --> 05:49.550
Zip it and crow.

05:49.551 --> 05:51.032
What, you're ignoring him now?

05:51.033 --> 05:53.550
- You're 12? No offense.
- None taken.

05:53.551 --> 05:56.550
Do you want me to do something about this?

05:56.551 --> 05:57.550
No. Absolutely not.

05:57.551 --> 05:58.938
I will deal with it later

05:58.939 --> 06:01.550
when I'm not teaching a lesson.

06:01.551 --> 06:03.550
There are two things that are bugging you.

06:03.551 --> 06:05.550
1, she was grinding her
crotch in his face,

06:05.551 --> 06:07.550
and 2, they slept together,
like, months ago,

06:07.551 --> 06:09.550
and they may still be boning.

06:09.551 --> 06:10.760
[bad note]

06:10.761 --> 06:12.550
Sorry.

06:12.551 --> 06:14.022
Duncan, I think that's actually

06:14.023 --> 06:15.550
all the time that we have for today.

06:15.551 --> 06:17.550
Well, here's the thing.

06:17.551 --> 06:19.550
My mom won't pay for
lessons with you anymore,

06:19.551 --> 06:22.751
so I was hoping I could pay with this.

06:24.551 --> 06:25.550
A stamp?

06:25.551 --> 06:27.550
It's a brown embossed SG 57

06:27.551 --> 06:30.550
from Great Britain, circa 1847.

06:30.551 --> 06:33.550
I predict it to be worth five lessons.

06:33.551 --> 06:35.550
Duncan, I don't even know
what to do with this.

06:35.551 --> 06:39.550
You eBay it. That shit's worth $500.

06:39.551 --> 06:42.751
Jesus. Deal.

06:43.551 --> 06:44.550
Oh.

06:44.551 --> 06:45.991
The course of conflict isn't determined

06:45.992 --> 06:47.551
by the person who initiates

06:47.552 --> 06:49.550
but by the person who responds.

06:49.551 --> 06:52.550
My parents do marriage counseling,

06:52.551 --> 06:54.550
even though they're not together anymore.

06:54.551 --> 06:56.751
Thank you, Duncan.

06:58.344 --> 06:59.550
- I'll see you soon.
- Bye.

06:59.551 --> 07:01.550
Don't talk to any
strangers on the subway.

07:01.551 --> 07:02.751
I won't.

07:09.551 --> 07:11.550
Betty: I shared an apartment
with two Hell's Angels

07:11.551 --> 07:13.550
down here in '79. Good times.

07:13.551 --> 07:15.751
Hi, Betty.

07:18.551 --> 07:20.550
- Hi.
- Hey.

07:20.551 --> 07:21.550
Oh. Let me...

07:21.551 --> 07:22.550
You will tell me next time

07:22.551 --> 07:24.550
he decides to pull
something like this, yes?

07:24.551 --> 07:26.751
I'll do my best, yes.

07:31.551 --> 07:33.550
Bienvenue!

07:33.551 --> 07:35.550
Welcome to the session.

07:35.551 --> 07:37.550
Hailey.

07:37.551 --> 07:38.550
Help me out.

07:38.551 --> 07:39.751
Everyone.

07:41.551 --> 07:42.550
Does this open?

07:42.551 --> 07:44.550
No, that's why I...

07:44.551 --> 07:46.751
Oh. Okay. All right.

07:48.551 --> 07:51.550
This is so goddamn wrong
on so many goddamn levels,

07:51.551 --> 07:54.550
- I can't even tell you.
- Welcome to the session, Bob.

07:54.551 --> 07:57.550
Oh. Cynthia, you're
wearing the bracelet, eh?

07:57.551 --> 07:58.550
Of course.

07:58.551 --> 08:00.550
Ah, and swift like a gazelle.

08:00.551 --> 08:04.550
I have metal kneecaps, so I
might as well use them, right?

08:04.551 --> 08:05.751
Nice one, D.D.

08:08.470 --> 08:10.751
- Mikael. Warren Boyd.
- Yeah.

08:11.551 --> 08:13.550
You're-you're... You're in.

08:13.551 --> 08:15.550
Svetlana, ah, watch it.

08:15.551 --> 08:16.550
Hello, Rennie.

08:16.551 --> 08:17.550
Hello. Hey, take care.

08:17.551 --> 08:19.550
You okay? Watch it, watch it

08:19.551 --> 08:21.877
because I can... Yeah. I can help.

08:23.551 --> 08:25.751
Now it's your turn. Go ahead.

08:27.551 --> 08:28.550
Watch it, watch it, watch it.

08:28.551 --> 08:29.550
- Hailey.
- Sorry.

08:29.551 --> 08:31.550
No, it's okay, it's okay.

08:31.551 --> 08:32.751
Okay.

08:34.551 --> 08:35.549
Oh.

08:35.551 --> 08:36.549
Yeah. You're free.

08:36.551 --> 08:37.549
Oh. Thanks.

08:37.551 --> 08:39.549
Okay.

08:39.551 --> 08:40.751
Good.

08:45.551 --> 08:48.550
Hello, Edward. I didn't
know you were a boxer.

08:48.551 --> 08:50.551
No, I'm not, but I train as one.

08:50.552 --> 08:52.550
I got a sparring partner and everything.

08:52.551 --> 08:53.550
Knocked him out by accident.

08:53.551 --> 08:55.751
He's fine now. He's a trouper.

08:56.551 --> 08:59.550
Mr. Beiben, your usual.

08:59.551 --> 09:01.550
No celery, extra carrots,
and raw Brussel sprouts.

09:01.551 --> 09:03.550
May I get you anything else?

09:03.551 --> 09:04.840
Uh, just bring my water, please.

09:04.841 --> 09:05.550
Thank you, Joel.

09:05.551 --> 09:06.869
Also, we're not going to eat this bread.

09:06.870 --> 09:08.550
Yes, sir.

09:08.551 --> 09:09.550
So, Gloria,

09:09.551 --> 09:12.550
I have got a 2:00
parent-teacher conference,

09:12.551 --> 09:14.550
so I'm afraid I'm going to have
to cut right to the chase.

09:14.551 --> 09:15.841
You look lovely, as always, by the way.

09:15.842 --> 09:17.549
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

09:17.551 --> 09:18.793
I was being interviewed yesterday

09:18.794 --> 09:20.551
for the Times business section,

09:20.552 --> 09:22.550
and the reporter mentioned
that our boy Rodrigo

09:22.551 --> 09:24.550
walked out on a Sunday magazine profile.

09:24.551 --> 09:26.550
Yeah, it's being rescheduled.

09:26.551 --> 09:29.919
I don't care. It was embarrassing. To me.

09:31.551 --> 09:33.550
I mean, Thomas Pembridge may
have lost his new car smell,

09:33.551 --> 09:36.550
but at least he was easy to drive.

09:36.551 --> 09:38.550
Edward, bringing Rodrigo here

09:38.551 --> 09:40.550
was a risk we knowingly took

09:40.551 --> 09:43.550
because the risk itself was
something we could market.

09:43.551 --> 09:44.550
Sexy and dangerous.

09:44.551 --> 09:47.550
You wanted a star. We got a comet.

09:47.551 --> 09:49.030
And don't worry. I have him under control.

09:49.031 --> 09:50.550
It doesn't look like it from here.

09:50.551 --> 09:52.550
Nothing sexy about a
train going off the rails.

09:52.551 --> 09:54.550
I don't want to fuck that.

09:54.551 --> 09:57.550
Look, he'd better prove

09:57.551 --> 09:59.550
that he can lead this damn orchestra.

09:59.551 --> 10:01.550
If not, I will advocate

10:01.551 --> 10:03.550
that Thomas be brought back next season.

10:03.551 --> 10:05.550
Thomas?

10:05.551 --> 10:07.550
You wanted me for my
business insight, Gloria.

10:07.551 --> 10:09.550
It's time you started running
this place like one.

10:09.551 --> 10:12.550
Classical music has been
losing money for people

10:12.551 --> 10:14.550
for 500 years.

10:14.551 --> 10:15.550
It's not a business.

10:15.551 --> 10:17.751
Everything's a business.

10:19.551 --> 10:21.550
So listen, at some point,

10:21.551 --> 10:23.191
I think you and I need
to schedule a meeting

10:23.192 --> 10:24.550
to sit down and talk face-to-face

10:24.551 --> 10:26.550
about, you know, Rodrigo and the orchestra.

10:26.551 --> 10:28.046
I'm confused. Aren't we having

10:28.047 --> 10:29.550
that exact meeting right now?

10:29.551 --> 10:31.550
No. It's parent-teacher conference time.

10:31.551 --> 10:33.551
Uh. Gloria Windsor, this is Ms. Alicia.

10:33.552 --> 10:35.550
Gloria runs the symphony for us,

10:35.551 --> 10:37.550
and Ms. Alicia's in charge
of my son's homeroom.

10:37.551 --> 10:41.550
Hey, why don't we schedule a
school trip to the symphony?

10:41.551 --> 10:42.550
Let them watch rehearsal.

10:42.551 --> 10:44.550
Yeah. That would be great.

10:44.551 --> 10:48.751
Yeah. The musicians love field trips.

10:49.551 --> 10:52.751
This humidity is fucked up.

10:53.551 --> 10:55.550
It's going to warp my wood.

10:55.551 --> 10:57.551
Christ, Bob. It's an instrument.

10:57.552 --> 10:59.751
It wants to be played.

11:02.551 --> 11:05.751
I think I'm going to take my shoes off.

11:06.551 --> 11:08.550
What are we doing here?

11:08.551 --> 11:10.961
I know many of you must have questions.

11:12.551 --> 11:17.550
We've got some earth here,
some city around us,

11:17.551 --> 11:19.550
people in their homes.

11:19.551 --> 11:22.550
Sometimes, when we lose our way,

11:22.551 --> 11:24.751
we must return to the basics.

11:25.551 --> 11:27.550
That's where the beauty lies.

11:27.551 --> 11:30.550
La bellesa de la vida.

11:30.551 --> 11:33.550
We're going to play a piece
that you all know very well.

11:33.551 --> 11:36.550
It's the La Obertura 1812.

11:36.551 --> 11:38.550
Tchaikovsky. Okay?

11:38.551 --> 11:41.550
What the hell's going on down there?
Who are you?

11:41.551 --> 11:43.751
We're the New York Symphony Orchestra.

11:44.551 --> 11:46.751
Ready?

11:47.551 --> 11:50.751
♪♪

12:40.551 --> 12:45.550
[screaming]

12:45.551 --> 12:46.751
Are you okay?

12:47.551 --> 12:50.550
No. No! No.

12:50.551 --> 12:52.551
I am not okay. I... I need help.

12:52.552 --> 12:56.550
I just can't keep being
jerked around like this!

12:56.551 --> 12:58.550
No. Mrs. Windsor,

12:58.551 --> 13:01.550
I see and hear a great deal
of things around here.

13:01.551 --> 13:04.550
The musicians, they smile
when they come to work.

13:04.551 --> 13:07.550
Not all, but more than before.

13:07.551 --> 13:09.550
He cares about us.

13:09.551 --> 13:12.550
He cares about himself.

13:12.551 --> 13:16.550
But that's good to hear.

13:16.551 --> 13:17.550
Thank you.

13:17.551 --> 13:20.550
I'm... I... I'm sorry.

13:20.551 --> 13:21.551
I'm so embarrassed.

13:21.552 --> 13:23.550
I seem to have forgotten your name.

13:23.551 --> 13:25.550
[chuckle] I'm Paviel.

13:25.551 --> 13:28.550
But they call me Pavel.

13:28.551 --> 13:31.550
- Pavel.
- Mm-hmm.

13:31.551 --> 13:32.550
It's a nice name.

13:32.551 --> 13:33.550
[chuckle]

13:33.551 --> 13:35.550
Thank you, Pavel.

13:35.551 --> 13:40.427
No. Thank you for bringing us the maestro.

13:40.428 --> 13:43.751
♪♪ ["1812 Overture"]

14:41.551 --> 14:43.550
- Ahh!
- [applause]

14:43.551 --> 14:45.751
Yeah!

14:46.551 --> 14:48.751
[cheering]

14:50.551 --> 14:51.550
Maestro!

14:51.551 --> 14:53.751
That was fun.

14:58.551 --> 14:59.550
Any questions?

14:59.551 --> 15:01.550
Uh, yeah. Where's the bathroom?

15:01.551 --> 15:04.751
- Uh, I have a question.
- Yes.

15:05.551 --> 15:06.550
What's this one?

15:06.551 --> 15:09.550
It's an oboe. Want to hold it?

15:09.551 --> 15:10.550
Sure.

15:10.551 --> 15:12.550
Don't be shy. Grab it like you mean it.

15:12.551 --> 15:14.751
[laughing]

15:16.551 --> 15:20.550
You do realize this was not a rehearsal.

15:20.551 --> 15:21.550
This was a performance.

15:21.551 --> 15:23.550
Yeah, and a really good one.

15:23.551 --> 15:24.550
No. It's...

15:24.551 --> 15:26.550
It's unsanctioned.

15:26.551 --> 15:29.550
Yeah. It's unsanctioned. It was unhinged.

15:29.551 --> 15:32.550
It was untethered, unclassified.

15:32.551 --> 15:34.550
It's earthy, it's happening,

15:34.551 --> 15:35.485
and I have never seen

15:35.486 --> 15:37.550
these rosy cheeks of yours.
Look at that. Look at that.

15:37.551 --> 15:39.550
- Thank you, maestro.
- I've never seen you like...

15:39.551 --> 15:40.550
[honking]

15:40.551 --> 15:42.550
Pizzas. Pizzas.

15:42.551 --> 15:44.052
Okay. Yes, for everybody, Bob.

15:44.053 --> 15:45.550
- Yes. Everyone...
- Pizza break.

15:45.551 --> 15:47.550
...whoever wants a slice, just go. Hailey.

15:47.551 --> 15:48.551
- Here.
- Hailey, Hailey,

15:48.552 --> 15:50.550
can you keep one for us?

15:50.551 --> 15:51.550
Yeah. Meat lover's?

15:51.551 --> 15:52.550
Meat lover? Meat lover?

15:52.551 --> 15:53.550
Meat lover's.

15:53.551 --> 15:55.550
Well, oh, okay, okay, fine.

15:55.551 --> 15:56.550
Good job.

15:56.551 --> 15:57.550
Thank you. Thank you.

15:57.551 --> 15:58.550
You, too. You, too.

15:58.551 --> 16:00.550
Just go. Go get it.

16:00.551 --> 16:02.550
Go get it. Go ahead.Go get some pizza.

16:02.551 --> 16:04.550
Go get some pizza, yes, everybody.

16:04.551 --> 16:08.751
♪♪ [Latin beat]

16:13.551 --> 16:15.550
Everyone is loving it, no?

16:15.551 --> 16:18.550
Yeah. This is amazing.

16:18.551 --> 16:20.550
I'm talking about the pizza.

16:20.551 --> 16:21.751
[laughs]

16:23.551 --> 16:25.550
Vete, Hailey.

16:25.551 --> 16:26.550
- Yeah?- Come.

16:26.551 --> 16:28.751
My God. Okay.

16:47.551 --> 16:49.550
[sucking in] You know, guys,

16:49.551 --> 16:51.550
I used to live right around the corner

16:51.551 --> 16:53.550
in the '70s.

16:53.551 --> 16:56.550
The decade. It was happening.

16:56.551 --> 16:57.751
♪♪

17:06.550 --> 17:09.751
[sirens]

17:12.550 --> 17:16.550
Man: Damn it! The cops!

17:16.550 --> 17:17.752
- The police?
- Yeah.

17:17.752 --> 17:20.207
The police? Okay. Wait there.

17:20.208 --> 17:21.550
- Who's in charge here?
- Wait there.

17:21.550 --> 17:22.968
Who's in charge?

17:22.969 --> 17:24.550
- I'm in charge.
- Ah, great.

17:24.550 --> 17:26.550
Who are you?

17:26.550 --> 17:27.550
My name is Rodrigo.

17:27.550 --> 17:29.550
Man: He's the maestro.

17:29.551 --> 17:30.550
Ah, good.

17:30.551 --> 17:31.550
Mr. Maestro, right?

17:31.551 --> 17:32.550
Yeah, you can call me like that.

17:32.551 --> 17:34.550
Can you tell me what you're doing here?

17:34.551 --> 17:36.550
Well, um, I took the orchestra

17:36.551 --> 17:38.550
for a field trip, you know,

17:38.551 --> 17:40.893
and because we play in the
August Memorial Symphony Hall

17:40.894 --> 17:42.224
and it's getting a little bit stuffy.

17:42.225 --> 17:43.550
I don't know if you've been there recently.

17:43.551 --> 17:45.550
Guys, guys, step back, please, all right?

17:45.551 --> 17:47.139
Step back, step back.

17:47.140 --> 17:49.550
So you just decided to take
everybody out on a little field trip

17:49.551 --> 17:51.550
to to have a block party.

17:51.551 --> 17:53.550
No, it's actually for everybody.

17:53.551 --> 17:55.551
It's all races. Everyone's welcome.

17:55.552 --> 17:57.550
It's the New York Symphony, pig.

17:57.551 --> 17:59.052
Hey, cool it.

17:59.053 --> 18:00.550
Steve.

18:00.551 --> 18:01.550
[crowd chatter]

18:01.551 --> 18:02.550
Are these your wire cutters?

18:02.551 --> 18:05.550
No. No, I borrowed them from Pavel.

18:05.551 --> 18:07.385
I don't care who you are.

18:07.386 --> 18:09.551
You're all trespassing.This
is private property.

18:09.552 --> 18:12.550
Can you please stop pissing
on the wall back there, sir?

18:12.551 --> 18:15.550
Who did this? Fold up this chair. Let's go.

18:15.551 --> 18:17.550
Move it on out. Come on. Move it out.

18:17.551 --> 18:19.551
- Let's go, let's go.
- Hang on, guys. Okay.

18:19.552 --> 18:21.550
We're going to keep this
under control, okay?

18:21.551 --> 18:23.550
- Drummer boy, pack it up.- Seriously?

18:23.551 --> 18:24.550
What was that, sir?

18:24.551 --> 18:26.550
I said "seriously"?

18:26.551 --> 18:28.550
You have nothing else better
to do with your time?

18:28.551 --> 18:31.551
I need you to pack it up.
Let's go. Guys, pick this up.

18:31.552 --> 18:33.550
With everything ugly out there,

18:33.551 --> 18:36.550
you have to break up something
so fucking beautiful?

18:36.551 --> 18:37.550
Is everything okay?

18:37.551 --> 18:39.550
- D.D.
- What?

18:39.551 --> 18:40.550
Take it easy.

18:40.551 --> 18:42.550
I got a right to speak my mind,

18:42.551 --> 18:44.550
unless you want to take that away also.

18:44.551 --> 18:46.550
Technically, he does have
the right of free speech.

18:46.551 --> 18:48.550
Right, my friend?

18:48.551 --> 18:49.550
Hey, don't touch that!

18:49.551 --> 18:50.550
[shouting]

18:50.551 --> 18:52.550
Officer, officer,

18:52.551 --> 18:54.404
he's very delicate with his instruments.

18:54.405 --> 18:56.037
- Please be careful, okay?
- You need to stay out of this.

18:56.038 --> 18:58.550
- My God! He's bending my arm!
- [shouting]

18:58.551 --> 19:00.550
Step back! Come on, now!

19:00.551 --> 19:02.968
Hey, hey! Come on, step back.

19:02.969 --> 19:05.550
Step back. Come on.

19:05.551 --> 19:07.550
I'm definitely not gonna go in that car.

19:07.551 --> 19:09.550
Fascists!

19:09.551 --> 19:10.550
All right, let's go. Right this way.

19:10.551 --> 19:12.751
All right.

19:16.551 --> 19:18.751
I've got one ready for processing.

19:20.551 --> 19:22.751
Open three.

19:29.551 --> 19:31.957
Excuse me.

19:31.958 --> 19:33.550
Have you given any thought
to our oboe lessons?

19:33.551 --> 19:35.550
You've got to be kidding me.

19:35.551 --> 19:37.550
No, I'm not. I'm a masochist, remember?

19:37.551 --> 19:39.550
[chuckles]

19:39.551 --> 19:41.135
I may have a slot available

19:41.136 --> 19:43.550
6:30 a.m. Saturday mornings.

19:43.551 --> 19:44.550
Great.

19:44.551 --> 19:45.551
My student just got a seat

19:45.552 --> 19:47.550
with the Kansas City Light Opera.

19:47.551 --> 19:49.751
I'll be there. Can't wait.

19:54.551 --> 19:58.550
Officer, I'll be sure to have him
back in time for the hearing.

19:58.551 --> 19:59.751
[shutter clicks]

20:01.551 --> 20:03.551
Thank you so much. Thank you for coming.

20:03.552 --> 20:05.550
Oh, and since we got some tickets,

20:05.551 --> 20:08.550
I think it's only fair
that you get some tickets

20:08.551 --> 20:09.550
to our upcoming season.

20:09.551 --> 20:11.550
Contact my office,

20:11.551 --> 20:13.093
and you and your guest
will be well cared for.

20:13.094 --> 20:14.550
Thank you.

20:14.551 --> 20:17.751
- Aw.
- Good manners, good manners, good manners.

20:22.551 --> 20:24.550
Uh, it's just up here on the right, please.

20:24.551 --> 20:25.751
- You got it.
- Thank you.

20:30.551 --> 20:33.751
Uh, um, here you go. Thank you.

20:37.551 --> 20:39.550
- Hey.
- Hey.

20:39.551 --> 20:40.551
Did you get my texts?

20:40.552 --> 20:43.550
I don't really want to seem
like some sort of stalker.

20:43.551 --> 20:45.469
No, I was just, like, super, super busy,

20:45.470 --> 20:46.550
so that's why I didn't call you back.

20:46.551 --> 20:48.550
- Okay.
- I'm sorry.

20:48.551 --> 20:50.751
Oh, no. It's okay.

20:53.551 --> 20:55.469
You're a really good choreographer.

20:55.470 --> 20:57.550
Okay. Thanks.

20:57.551 --> 20:59.897
I mean, do you only take calls

20:59.898 --> 21:01.550
from... from bad choreographers?

21:01.551 --> 21:03.550
Because, you know, if that is the case...

21:03.551 --> 21:05.751
- No.
- ...I will try to suck more.

21:10.551 --> 21:12.751
I saw you sleeping in Addison's bed.

21:14.551 --> 21:15.551
It's stupid. I just...

21:15.552 --> 21:18.550
I was watching TV in her
room waiting up for you,

21:18.551 --> 21:19.550
and I fell asleep.

21:19.551 --> 21:21.751
Okay.

21:23.551 --> 21:25.751
Okay.

21:27.551 --> 21:29.751
I know. Sorry. That...

21:31.551 --> 21:33.550
Well, I don't know

21:33.551 --> 21:35.550
if this is the best timing,

21:35.551 --> 21:38.550
but, uh, I, uh...

21:38.551 --> 21:40.550
I was going to actually invite you

21:40.551 --> 21:41.550
to come with me to Florida.

21:41.551 --> 21:42.550
- Really?
- Yeah.

21:42.551 --> 21:44.550
Why?

21:44.551 --> 21:45.551
Well, so I guess he was

21:45.552 --> 21:47.550
a modeling agent or something,

21:47.551 --> 21:48.551
came to my showcase

21:48.552 --> 21:51.550
and needed a dancer for a body spray ad,

21:51.551 --> 21:53.550
and yeah, he, uh, scouted me for the gig.

21:53.551 --> 21:55.550
- Oh, my God.
- Yeah.

21:55.551 --> 21:57.550
Wow. Um...

21:57.551 --> 22:00.550
uh...

22:00.551 --> 22:02.550
Florida.

22:02.551 --> 22:03.711
Um...

22:04.551 --> 22:06.751
I can't.

22:08.551 --> 22:09.550
I have, um...

22:09.551 --> 22:12.550
an oboe lesson at 6:30 in the morning.

22:12.551 --> 22:14.550
I know that sounds really ridiculous,

22:14.551 --> 22:16.550
but the lady who's giving them to me

22:16.551 --> 22:17.760
is really amazing,

22:17.761 --> 22:19.551
and she just, like, fucking hates my guts,

22:19.552 --> 22:21.550
so it's the only time that she agreed...

22:21.551 --> 22:23.550
- Yeah, yeah.
- ...to teach me, so...

22:23.551 --> 22:24.751
- Okay.
- Yeah.

22:25.551 --> 22:26.550
6:30 in the morning.

22:26.551 --> 22:28.550
Yeah. I know. It's horrible.

22:28.551 --> 22:29.550
It sucks.

22:29.551 --> 22:31.302
But it's really a big deal,

22:31.303 --> 22:34.751
and I just... I got to focus right now.

22:36.551 --> 22:38.550
Yeah, I'd love to hang out when I get back.

22:38.551 --> 22:40.550
- Okay.
- Yeah.

22:40.551 --> 22:42.751
All right. Have fun with your lessons.

22:54.551 --> 22:57.751
Gloria, can I tell you something?

22:59.551 --> 23:01.550
You should have seen them out there.

23:01.551 --> 23:04.260
It was incredible. It was beautiful.

23:04.261 --> 23:05.550
They were... Oh, my God.

23:05.551 --> 23:07.550
I've retained legal counsel
from Leonard Bernstein...

23:07.551 --> 23:09.550
not that one...

23:09.551 --> 23:11.550
who reminds me

23:11.551 --> 23:15.550
your O1 visa could be affected

23:15.551 --> 23:16.550
by your little adventure.

23:16.551 --> 23:18.551
You could be deported, Rodrigo.

23:18.552 --> 23:22.550
Oh, and I thought you'd like to see this

23:22.551 --> 23:23.550
from our friend Union Bob.

23:23.551 --> 23:26.550
An invoice for $80,000 overtime,

23:26.551 --> 23:28.550
including a performance bonus.

23:28.551 --> 23:32.052
Ah, it's okay. I'll pay it.
I'll pay it personally.

23:32.053 --> 23:33.551
Okay, but that's not the point.

23:33.552 --> 23:36.550
It's a small price to pay
for something so valuable.

23:36.551 --> 23:38.255
Really, it was the first time that I felt

23:38.256 --> 23:39.550
that we were getting at
something, you know?

23:39.551 --> 23:41.550
That we were reaching some place.

23:41.551 --> 23:44.550
Rodrigo, I am a true believer

23:44.551 --> 23:49.550
in your art, your attitude,
your excitement, you.

23:49.551 --> 23:51.550
I'm going to be straight with you.

23:51.551 --> 23:55.550
Our orchestra is in serious
financial trouble,

23:55.551 --> 23:57.550
deep financial trouble.

23:57.551 --> 24:00.550
You understand what I'm saying?

24:00.551 --> 24:02.751
Yeah.

